; Aury v0 example: effect violation.
; `leak-rng` is declared `pure` but calls `rng.next`, which requires the `rng`
; capability. The effect checker rejects this with EFFECT_EXCEEDS_DECLARED
; and proposes adding the missing capability.

(module effects-bad
  (fn leak-rng
    (params (a i64))
    (ret i64)
    (body
      (call i64.add (ref a) (call rng.next))))
)